:QUOTE [subtitle:Eckhart Tolle, quotetype:PLAIN]
Realize deeply that the present moment is all you ever have.

:INFO
Reading With My Skepticism Intact
I came to The Power of Now expecting to argue with it. I am not a spiritual person \
by nature, and books about presence and consciousness make me uneasy. I finished it \
anyway because a friend I respect told me to stay past chapter three. She was right \
about chapter three. The ideas that stayed were not the mystical ones. They were \
about the space between a thought and your reaction to it.

:NOTE
The chapter on the pain-body is the one I return to most.

:JOURNEY
Reading The Power of Now
Section
Resonance
- Chapters 1 and 2 | 2 | Too abstract | Felt unreachable and I nearly stopped
- Chapter 3 onward | 4 | Shifted | Stopped fighting the language and let it in
- Pain body concept | 3 | Loosely defined | Useful framing but hard to fully trust
- Relationship chapters | 4 | Surprisingly concrete | More applicable than expected

